im, saying, Lord, behold, he whom thou lovest is sick.","year":33},{"id":"recdfucFPhoSWhQcX","ref":"John.11.4","text":"When Jesus heard that, he said, This sickness is not unto death, but for the glory of God, that the Son of God might be glorified thereby.","year":33},{"id":"rechR22pxCYnnqnUD","ref":"John.11.5","text":"Now Jesus loved Martha, and her sister, and Lazarus.","year":33},{"id":"reci1YVHCOtNHGF27","ref":"John.11.6","text":"When he had heard therefore that he was sick, he abode two days still in the same place where he was.","year":33},{"id":"recCdyaOokVCPJJc3","ref":"John.11.7","text":"Then after that saith he to his disciples, Let us go into Judaea again.","year":33},{"id":"recbgfHtGMfx8m30z","ref":"John.11.8","text":"His disciples say unto him, Master, the Jews of late sought to stone thee; and goest thou thither again?","year":33}]}
